name: ~ Kiran Punjabi Raichura
message: Right to LandIf a person loses his/her right of abode in the HKSAR he/she will automatically acquire the right to land in the HKSAR in accordance with the law, which will allow he/she enjoys the right:To land in the HKSAR;To be free from any condition of stay (including a limit of stay) in the HKSAR; andNot to be removed from the HKSAR.He/She will be able to enter the HKSAR freely to live, study and work without any restriction.

name: ~ STAY POSITIVE IN LIFE
message: https://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking-news/section/4/192247/Citizens-angry-as-many-ineligible-for-Consumption-VoucherThe second phase of the Consumption Voucher Scheme will be issued on August 7. A reader of Sing Tao Daily, surnamed Wong, complained that she was told by the government she doesn’t have the eligibility to receive the vouchers.As Wong sought to immigrate in 2011, she has withdrawn the Mandatory Provident Fund (MPF). She flew back the next year and works in Hong Kong for the last ten years. She keeps paying the taxes as well as contributing to a new MPF. Wong is angry and annoyed after an official SMS telling her she is ineligible for the Consumption Voucher.The government stated that if citizens have permanently left Hong Kong or are intending to leave Hong Kong, they will lose their eligibility for the consumption voucher. A spokesperson added that some may lose their eligibility if they applied to withdraw their MPF early due to permanent departure from the city.

name: ~ STAY POSITIVE IN LIFE
message: Who can notarize documents in Hong Kong?Notary PublicWho can notarise in Hong Kong? Generally, a Notary Public may be described as an officer of the law whose public office duty it is to draw up, attest or certify certain documents under their signature and official seal. Notaries Public are usually experienced solicitors who have been practicing for at least 7 years.

name: ~ STAY POSITIVE IN LIFE
message: How can I get notarized in Hong Kong?There are two ways in which a document can be authenticated. One is to go through a Notary Public to notarize, the other is to apostille with a seal from the High Court. To help you understand the Notarization process in Hong Kong, and the specific documents required , this article has been specially prepared for you.

message: Dear AllComplete details as requested by many This is prepared by *Ms. Deepthi* - for our HELP GROUP members .  She is one of the ADMINS of our Flight group and also  she helped many stranded Indians on expired visa issues teaming up with Ms. Betty *Thanking her for offering help and taking time to prepare this -on behalf of HELP GROUP ADMINS TEAM*School allocation:*a. Initiation program b. Primary School c. Secondary school*• WHAT IS INITIATION PROGRAM?Induction Programme for Newly Arrived ChildrenTo help the newly arrived children cope with adjustment problems and learning difficulties which they generally encounter when they are newly joining the local education system, the Education Bureau has introduced an Induction Programme for the children newly arrived from the Mainland and for the newly arrived non-Chinese speaking (NCS) children & returnee children since April 1995 and October 2000 respectively.• Links to check for initiation program :• INTRODUCTION: https://www.edb.gov.hk/en/student-parents/newly-arrived-children/about-newly-arrived-children/index.html• ALL INFO REGARDING INITIATION PROGRAM IS IN THE ABOVE LINK.• SCHOOL LIST IN THE INITIATION PROGRAM: https://www.edb.gov.hk/en/student-parents/newly-arrived-children/initiation-program/school-list.html*REGULAR SCHOOL FOR PRIMARY AND SECONDARY:**TYPES OF SCHOOL IN HONG KONG* :  a.  Government schoolb. Direct Subsidy Schoolsc. Private Schoolse. International Schools• LINK TO CHECK SCHOOL INFORMATION AND SCHOOL DETAILS: https://www.edb.gov.hk/en/student-parents/sch-info/sch-search/index.html• INFORMATION WITHIN THE ABOVE LINK: - Kindergarten, Primary & Secondary School Profiles- School Information Search & School Lists- Education for Non-Chinese Speaking Children- Information Sheet and Prospectus - Fees & Charges in Schools- School Fees of DSS Schools- Incorporated Management Committee (IMC)- School Management Committee- Vacancy Situation of Schools• LINK TO CHECKLIST OF SCHOOLS BY DISTRICT: https://www.edb.gov.hk/en/student-parents/sch-info/sch-search/schlist-by-district/index.html• INFORMATION WITHIN THE ABOVE LINK:- School Search (Schools which are not yet registered are excluded)- School Lists (By District) (2020/21)- List of "Through-train" Schools- List of Schools Offering Full-time Initiation Programme for Newly Arrived Children- THE ABOVE INFORMATION IS VERY DETAILED GIVING INFOR ABOUT TYPE OF SCHOOL, STRUCTURE OF EDUCATION, SUBJECTS IN THE LANGUAGE TAUGHT. - YOU ALSO HAVE A SEARCH OPTION WITHIN THE LINK TO CHECK SPECIFIC DETAILS. - EDB is very forthcoming and very helpful, you can always approach them for any information and they are happy to guide you through the way.*Contact for EDB:*>1. Can connect with EDB by sending a query on this *link* https://www.edb.gov.hk/en/contact-us/index.html>2. *Email*edbinfo@edb.gov.hk (for enquiries) or edbcomp@edb.gov.hk (for complaints)>3. Or by *personally meeting* them at the below addressAddress15/F, Wu Chung House 213 Queen's Road East Wan Chai, Hong Kong>4. OR *CALLING* THEM AT :Tel(852) 2891 0088Fax(852) 2893 0858*PLEASE REMEMBER THE CONTACT DETAILS FOR KINDERGARTEN ARE DIFFERENT*FromADMIN*HELP GROUP HK*

name: ~ Kumar
message: From your first VISA Sticker of work employment or otherwise the date is calculated from actual date of entry the visa labels should have no break in between if it is 7 years you will be eligible to apply for permanent resident, 6 months consecutive stay out of hong kong is fine i was out for 10 months during covid in 2021 however if they ask you the reasons you should be able to reply

message: FREE OIL PASTEL ART WORKSHOP FOR PEOPLE WITH DISABILITIES! | IN-PERSON AND ZOOM OPTIONS AVAILABLE  Join us on 29th August from 1:30 to 3:30 PM for a complimentary oil pastel art workshop at Kowloon Cricket Club! Organised by SENsational Foundation and International Women's Peace Group (IWPC), the workshop is open to people of all disabilities, ages and skill level. We hope to promote the inclusion of people with disabilities in the creative arts, and to provide the participants with the tools to explore and express their creative sides. So join us for an afternoon of arts and crafts!  If you are interested in participating, please register by emailing us at contact@sensationalhk.org! The cut-off date for registration is 27th August.

name: ~ Deepti
message: John Lee Press Conference on Cancellation of Hotel Quarantine: Last updated at 1620 on 9/23: Mr. John Lee: New Measures Introduced by Hong Kong Government. 1) All arrivals at HKIA Quarantine measures will be changed to 0+3 effective Monday, Sep 26 at 0600hrs. 2) Pre-Flight PCR will be scrapped. This has been replaced by a RAT test to be taken within 24-hours of flight departure time. There is a need for a Day 2, Day 4 and Day 6 PCR test. 3) Unvaccinated or partially vaccinated Hong Kong Residents can return. 4) No quota on return to Hong Kong Scheme ------------------------------------------0+3 Scheme: • Quarantine hotels will be scrapped. • People can return directly home or go to any hotel of his/her choice to undergo 3 day medical surveillance.• There will be a PCR test at the airport and there is no need to wait for the result. Test and Go arrangement. • All passengers can use any form of public transport• After the airport test is negative an amber code will be sent to the handphone of the passenger. • On day 3 after a negative PCR test a blue code will be sent to the passenger. • A daily rat test must be taken for the first 7 days too. • If positive you can quarantine at your hotel or home. If you home is not suitable, you can still choose to ask the Hong Kong Government to invite you to one of their quarantine facilities. ------------------------------------------Pre-Flight PCR will be scrapped:• RAT test must be taken within 24 hours of departure time. • Sounds like it needs to the test needs to be uploaded to HKGOV prior to boarding. ------------------------------------------Unvaccinated Hong Kong Residents can return: • Unvaccinated or those who have not completed their vaccinations can board a plane to Hong Kong. • After they have landed in Hong Kong no special exemptions will be made. They will have to follow the current Hong Kong laws to get a vaccine pass like everyone else. The Hong Kong Government will not lie flat and they will continue to control the number of cases in the community. The Government plans to protect the elderly, children and the vulnerable. Hong Kong should be optimistic about controlling the epidemic. ------------------------------------------Professor Lo Chung-Mau: • Prof Lo has data that can show you why 0+3 will not increase risk compared to 0+0. • The one reason for 0+3 and the PCR tests is because The Hong Kong Government does not want new variants to enter the community.• Hong Kong is following a science based approach • He thanks all those involved including the general public in taking vaccinations this year. The number of those fully vaccinated persons have greatly increased compared to earlier this year. • The young and old need extra protection. • The R value is currently less than 1 and community testing centers are seeing a downward trend. • Professor Lo believes the Omicron Ba. 5 spread is under control• Starting 8/22 (3+4 Introduction Date) visitor numbers have increased. • About 3.3% of inbound visitors are positive compared to the earlier 4.7%• Global figures are falling. • Law enforcement have not found any amber code persons trying to enter restricted premises. ------------------------------------------Mr. John Lee: • He wants to control the overall epidemic situation in an orderly way. • The Government will monitor the situation closely, so all the risks are controlled and things can progress in an orderly manner. • If there are positive developments as we progress, there will be more room for more activities to open up. • Visitors will come as we are a free economy, a place of opportunities, a place of east meets west, a place of success stories and a place where you can use HK to open a base to The Mainland. • After the 3rd day you can do everything a Hong Kong Citizen does including eat and drink out.https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202209/23/P2022092300651.htm

name: ~ Anandhakannan

name: ~ Deepti
message: John Lee Press Conference on Cancellation of Hotel Quarantine: Last updated at 1620 on 9/23: Mr. John Lee: New Measures Introduced by Hong Kong Government. 1) All arrivals at HKIA Quarantine measures will be changed to 0+3 effective Monday, Sep 26 at 0600hrs. 2) Pre-Flight PCR will be scrapped. This has been replaced by a RAT test to be taken within 24-hours of flight departure time. There is a need for a Day 2, Day 4 and Day 6 PCR test. 3) Unvaccinated or partially vaccinated Hong Kong Residents can return. 4) No quota on return to Hong Kong Scheme ------------------------------------------0+3 Scheme: • Quarantine hotels will be scrapped. • People can return directly home or go to any hotel of his/her choice to undergo 3 day medical surveillance.• There will be a PCR test at the airport and there is no need to wait for the result. Test and Go arrangement. • All passengers can use any form of public transport• After the airport test is negative an amber code will be sent to the handphone of the passenger. • On day 3 after a negative PCR test a blue code will be sent to the passenger. • A daily rat test must be taken for the first 7 days too. • If positive you can quarantine at your hotel or home. If you home is not suitable, you can still choose to ask the Hong Kong Government to invite you to one of their quarantine facilities. ------------------------------------------Pre-Flight PCR will be scrapped:• RAT test must be taken within 24 hours of departure time. • Sounds like it needs to the test needs to be uploaded to HKGOV prior to boarding. ------------------------------------------Unvaccinated Hong Kong Residents can return: • Unvaccinated or those who have not completed their vaccinations can board a plane to Hong Kong. • After they have landed in Hong Kong no special exemptions will be made. They will have to follow the current Hong Kong laws to get a vaccine pass like everyone else. The Hong Kong Government will not lie flat and they will continue to control the number of cases in the community. The Government plans to protect the elderly, children and the vulnerable. Hong Kong should be optimistic about controlling the epidemic. ------------------------------------------Professor Lo Chung-Mau: • Prof Lo has data that can show you why 0+3 will not increase risk compared to 0+0. • The one reason for 0+3 and the PCR tests is because The Hong Kong Government does not want new variants to enter the community.• Hong Kong is following a science based approach • He thanks all those involved including the general public in taking vaccinations this year. The number of those fully vaccinated persons have greatly increased compared to earlier this year. • The young and old need extra protection. • The R value is currently less than 1 and community testing centers are seeing a downward trend. • Professor Lo believes the Omicron Ba. 5 spread is under control• Starting 8/22 (3+4 Introduction Date) visitor numbers have increased. • About 3.3% of inbound visitors are positive compared to the earlier 4.7%• Global figures are falling. • Law enforcement have not found any amber code persons trying to enter restricted premises. ------------------------------------------Mr. John Lee: • He wants to control the overall epidemic situation in an orderly way. • The Government will monitor the situation closely, so all the risks are controlled and things can progress in an orderly manner. • If there are positive developments as we progress, there will be more room for more activities to open up. • Visitors will come as we are a free economy, a place of opportunities, a place of east meets west, a place of success stories and a place where you can use HK to open a base to The Mainland. • After the 3rd day you can do everything a Hong Kong Citizen does including eat and drink out.https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202209/23/P2022092300651.htm

name: ~ Kulbir Don Singh
message: As you may be aware, a person must have a "PCR testing registration code" to receive free PCR test on or after 1 November.Otherwise you will be charged HK$150 or HK$240 per test.To avoid incurring unnecessary cost, please complete the registration on or before 31 October (Mon) via your LeaveHomeSafe App, which is easy and quick:1. Open your LeaveHomeSafe App2. Slide to the right3. The third page is "PCR Testing Registration Code"4. Click and complete all the requested information (e.g. name, address, HKID)5. Press "Confirmed" and then you will receive a QR Code6. Registration completed’

name: ~ Shravs
message: U need to do a RAT test 24hrs before ur flight departure. On arrival at HK Airport, once u get off the air craft they will do RT PCR test. You need to show the QR code generated by you by filling in all details before ur flight departure on the chp site.

name: ~ STAY POSITIVE IN LIFE
message: CO Op*Attention Mumbai Flat Owners, No NOC Needed From Housing Society To Sell/Rent Flats Now*  - Minister Shares BIG UpdateMaharashtra Housing Minister Dr Jitendra Awhad said that as per the by-laws, the society's permissions are not required for owners to either sell/hire out their homes, yet many managing committees are insisting on their clearance – Mumbai - In a big news for Mumbai flat owners, Maharashtra Housing Minister Dr Jitendra Awhad on Tuesday announced that from now on - no prior permission or no objection certificate (NOC) from a cooperative housing society would be necessary for owners wanting to sell/rent out their flats. This would enable the owners to conduct his/her rental/sale transactions without hassles or delays and prevent harassment by the society committees to green signal such proposals, the minister said - “We have come to know that many housing societies discriminate on the basis of caste, creed, religion, community, vegetarians and don’t permit the owners to sell/rent out their properties,” Dr Awhad said. He pointed out how in some societies or localities dominated by any particular community, certain communities are barred in the name of preferring only ‘vegetarians’, or preventing Dalits and Other Backward Classes, which is leading to increasing hatred among the people - He said as per the by-laws, the society’s permissions are not required for owners to either sell/hire out their homes, yet many managing committees are insisting on their clearance. “Now, if the owner wishes to sell-rent out his flat, he/she will not need the society’s NOC,”  Dr Awhad declared, justifying it on grounds of Mumbai being a leading cosmopolitan city in the world and such tactics were sullying the image of the country’s financial capital.Decision welcomed by many - Several individuals, societies, and the Maharashtra Societies Welfare Association have approved and welcomed Dr Awhad’s initiative, and urged that it should be formalised through a ‘Government Resolution’ with punitive clauses for the errant societies/managing committee members.- There have been many instances in the past when people, including many celebs, were barred from buying/selling flats in certain areas/housing societies under the garb of the NOC,  but now that will stop, said a Kandivali CHS Chairman, preferring anonymity. “Consequently, many lose out on a potentially lucrative deal, their transactions get delayed in the societal red-tapism, some societies even demand a certain amount of the deal as a ‘donation’ to the building funds, and there was harassment of both the buyers and the sellers on various counts,” he said.https://www.india.com/maharashtra/attention-mumbai-flat-owners-no-noc-from-housing-society-to-sell-rent-flats-needed-now-minister-shares-big-update-5334502/

ALBERT AU PRESS CONFERENCE SUMMARY*-------------------------------- *COVID-19 Update*DR. AU UPDATE:•	There has been a 28.6% increase in total cases from the week before. •	Imported cases have rise 5.7% from the week before. •	Imported cases represents about 7% of all all cases in Hong Kong. •	About 55% of imported cases are tested positive on arrival at HKIA. The remaining 45% test positive from days 1-7. •	There are other variants being found locally now including XBB.•	Globally BQ.1 and XBB variants are on the rise.•	Case numbers are rising in care homes and schools. •	Death raises remain stable. ---------------------------------*HOSPITAL AUTHORITY*•	Around 2300 Positive cases admitted in Hospital •	Around 290 new patients admitted for Covid daily. •	More than 90 patients in serious or critical condition. ---------------------------------*HKGOV Update*Testing for passengers arriving in Hong Kong: Starting at 0001 hours on November 21, 2022•	All passengers arriving from outside Mainland China and Taiwan will be required to do two PCR tests. The first test will be administered on arrival at the airport on Day 0. The second PCR test will need to be taken on Day 2 at a community testing center. All passengers will still be required to conduct a RAT test from Days 1-7. •	For passengers that arrive on Nov 21st and thereafter, you  will no longer be required to go and take a per test on Days 4 and Days 6.*Vaccine Pass* •	Beginning on Nov 30, those aged between 5-11 must have taken two doses of a vaccine.  Those aged 12 and above must have taken three doses of a vaccine to meet the vaccine pass requirement. •	Those who have been issued a medical exemption certificate. These individuals may be deemed fit for vaccination after a medical assessment. If this is the case the a transitional vaccine pass will be issued. *BioNTech Bivalent Vaccine* •	This new vaccine has been approved by the Government scientific committee on vaccines for emergency use.•	Hong Kong has procured this vaccine and the earliest arrival time is at the end of the month.English press release:https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202211/17/P2022111700682.htm

name: ~ STAY POSITIVE IN LIFE
message: https://www.timesofisrael.com/israeli-scientists-find-running-reduces-chance-of-some-cancers-by-72/People who regularly run or engage in other aerobic exercise cut their chance of developing some cancers by 72 percent, according to research from Tel Aviv University.Aerobic exercise makes some organs so efficient at grabbing sugar that is in the body that tumors are left starved of glucose, and often unable to grow and spread, the peer-reviewed study published last week suggested.It focused on metastatic cancer, meaning cancer that has spread from its original location in the body. Researchers believe there are also strong benefits in preventing primary tumors, but focused on metastatic cancer as it is Israel’s leading cause of death.“Physical activity is creating a hostile setting for tumors by creating an environment where it has difficulty obtaining glucose,” lead author Prof. Carmit Levy, from the Tel Aviv University’s Department of Human Genetics and Biochemistry, told The Times of Israel.“We showed in this study that running and other aerobic activity protects the body from metastatic activity, and discovered what mechanism makes this happen.”

name: ~ Karen Purswaney HK
message: Thank you for supporting the Refugee Union, Hong Kong's only self-organized refugee group. We are a collaborative effort between YOU & US  🤗Please follow us on social media and share this message with friends and online as the best way to create awareness and support us 🙏Facebook: @Refugee Unionhttps://www.facebook.com/refugeeunion/Instagram: @refugeeunionhttps://instagram.com/refugeeunionWebsite: www.refugeeunion.org🏢 Address: Unit E, 2 Floor, Lee Fung Building, 315-319 Queen’s Road Central, Sheung Wan 🚆 MTR Exit A2  🚪 Gate code: R9877🕑 Office Hours: Monday to Saturday 10am to 6pmCLOSED on Sundays and Public HolidaysNo appointment needed during opening hours 🏃✅ We are grateful for used clothes and shoes (baby, children and adults); bed linens, quilts and pillows; baby formula all stages, diapers all ages and strollers; kitchen utensils, pots and cutlery and crockery; dried and canned food; mobile phones and small electronics; any kind of toiletries, soap, shampoo and detergent; English books for all ages; surgical masks for adults and children. Some children toys are welcome.❌ We don't take any furniture, carpets, mattresses, baby cribs and high chairs, curtains, crutches, clothes hangers, car seats and decorative items. Our subdivided rooms are too small. 😞 Sorry we do not collect except in Sheung Wan🙏We are most thankful for laptops, mobile phones, small fridges, washing machines, microwaves, rice-cookers, kettles, televisions and window-type aircons. 🚐 For large donations please consider sending a Gogo van and advising the delivery time. Call in the morning for the name and number of the person in charge. Sorry but we don’t have money to pay for transportation 😓💵 CASH is a priority as we are not allowed to work and our wallets are empty. As refugees we are unable to open a society bank account, so please donate to "Drink For Justice" a registered charity which will disburses the funds to us www.drinkforjustice.org🌟 Our Wish list is: 1. cash; 2. milk formula; 3. diapers; 4. mobile phones; 5. rice-cookers; 6. bags of rice; 7. UHT milk; 8. laptops🚨 Refugees do not receive sufficient welfare yet we are prohibited from working with the threat of 22.5 months in prison, 15 months with a guilty plea. So we live in poverty and must beg for community assistance 😟For more information please click:- https://bit.ly/3FouVOg- https://bit.ly/38FjT9x - https://bit.ly/3qqiQUu

name: ~ Deepti
message: Dec 28 -Anti-epidemic Command and Coordination Group Press Conference hosted by Chief Executive, Mr. John Lee. Relaxation of Epidemic Measures: Effective at 0001hrs on December 29th, 2022. 1.	Cancellation of Quarantine orders. The Govenment will no  longer going trace close contacts. Hong Kong Government will continue to give assistance and advice to those who test positive. 2.	Cancellation of Vaccine Pass. The Hong Kong Government will continue to push for high vaccination rates within the community. 3.	Cancellation of All PCR Testing. The cancellation will mean arrivals from everywhere including outside of Mainland China will no longer be required to test. Travelers will continue to be required to take a RAT test daily for 5 days after arriving in Hong Kong. 4.	Cancellation of All Social Distancing Measures. 5.	Masks mandate will remain. The Government has come to this conclusion after considering the following: 1.	The very high vaccination rate of the population2.	Over 2.5 million people have been previously infected with Covid 193.	Hong Kong has a sufficient supply of effective medications to treat Covid-19. 4.	Health personnel understand how to deal with Covid-19 after three years of experience. 5.	The Hospital Authority capacity to deal with Covid-19 has been greatly improved. 6.	With 3 years of experience, Hong Kong people have a very good understanding and well equipped to protect themselves from Covid-19. 7.	Anti-Epidemic Measures will focus on protecting high risk groups. These include those who live in elderly homes as well as the old and the young. These measures are to help Hong Kong return to normalcy. Professor Lo Chung-mau - Secretary of Health:•	The Government has been taking gradual steps to resume normalcy in Hong Kong. Quarantine Order and Close Contacts: 1.	There will be no more defined close contacts and quarantine orders. We have been fighting the Covid-19 virus for three years and we have a high vaccination rate, an increasing level of immunity barrier within the community. The capacity to tackle the epidemic challenges has been enhanced. Family members of positive cases of confirmed cases and other closes contacts will not be placed under testing or quarantine arrangements. Department of Health will issue advice to positive cases as well as to their family members. 2.	Quarantine orders will be stopped as of tomorrow and those in quarantine facilities will be released tomorrow. 3.	Isolation arrangements for positive cases will remain the same. The Government will closely monitor the epidemic and will adjust the measures when necessary. 4.	Government will no longer send out anti epidemic kits to close contacts. Confirmed cases will continue to receive anti epidemic kits. Vaccine Pass:The Government has decided to cancel the vaccine pass system under Cap 599L. 1.	Since the introduction, it has been effective and it has successfully raised the vaccination rate to a high level. 2.	83% of residents in Hong Kong have had at least three doses.3.	The Government will look for more targeted measures to the elderly and the young. Testing for inbound travelers: ALL PCR Testing has been cancelled. 1.	Taking into account to resume the flow of people from Mainland and Hong Kong. 2.	Hong Kong will streamline the rules to All travelers including those from Mainland China. 3.	All Inbound travelers must do a RAT test 24 prior to departure of a PCR test no more than 48 hours prior to departure. 4.	Health Declaration form will be cancelled however if the inbound traveler still wants to electronically submit one then he/she is free to do so. 5.	A photograph copy of the travelers RAT or PCR result should be kept in case a health officer asks for proof during an inspection.6.	Health advice will be issued to all arriving passengers. 7.	A Rat test is required from Day 1-5 upon arrival. Social Distancing Measures: 1.	All social distancing measures have been cancelled. 2.	All measures under Cap 599F and Cap 599G will be removed.3.	Mask mandate remains under Cap 599I. Mask wearing can protect yourself and those around you. Hong Kong is now in a high flu season. Experts believe that getting rid of the mask mandate will cause a lot of disease and The Government must protect the healthcare system. Arrangement of Local Medical Resources: 1.	Local people will have priority in the healthcare system. 2.	Hospital Authority (HA) has been enhancing its capacity.3.	HA will continue ask private healthcare to support them. 4.	Paxlovid and other drugs have been given to private clinics and hospitals. This can help lessen the burden on the public system5.	HA will provide services and drugs to local residents. Tourists and non residents cannot use designated clinics. Non eligible persons will also provide treatment to urgent treatments and those will be charged a higher rate. 6.	HA will keep a good supply of pain and fever medicine like paracetamol. Department of Health will make sure there is sufficient stock. 7.	Private sector can now order the two types of covid medicines from the manufacturers. Those who are not Hong Kong residents will need to pay $6000. 8.	The objective and policy is to make sure there is always a sufficient supply of vaccinations for Hong Kong Residents. 9.	Government will not offer Government procured vaccines to non Hong Kong residents. Private sector may do so. Summary: 1.	Covid transmission is still high if you look at the waste water samples. 2.	Covid together with Flu will put pressure on the healthcare system. The old and young needs to be protected. 3.	Sewage surveillance program will continue. 4.	Random tests for genome sequencing will be carried out from testing centers to look for variants of concern. 5.	Everyone needs to work together. •	Get vaccinated •	Wear your mask •	Protect high risk groups.Live Feed: https://webcast.info.gov.hk/revamp/eng/livecast.html

message: 28 Dec 20:01: COVID Control Measures For Arrivals (Govt P/R, translated from Chinese)https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202212/28/P2022122800679.htmThis press release affects passengers arrived since 27 Dec.Effective from 29 Dec:VACCINATION•	Must omplete a Suggested dosage (usually 2) of Recognised vaccines ( https://www.coronavirus.gov.hk/pdf/list_of_recognised_covid19_vaccines.pdf ). Exemption: 1.	Aged 11 or lower - requirement waived2.	Aged 12-17: One dose of BioNTech Comirnaty accepted3.	Hong Kong Residents - requirement waived4.	Arrivals who have only stayed in Mainland China and/or Macau in past 7 days - requirement waived•	(Provisional) Vaccine Pass will become obsolete and no longer issuedPRE-DEPARTURE TESTING•	Rapid Antigen / Lateral Flow Test (RAT): 24 hours before take off (or arrival at Border Control Point), can be administered by the passenger themselves.•	Result may be declared ( https://www.chp.gov.hk/hdf ); or must keep photo proof for a 90-day period for checking.•	Passengers may opt for PCR test within 48 hours before flight takes off / arrival at border.AFTER TOUCH DOWN IN HONG KONG•	All PCR testing scrapped•	Last compulsory testing date = 28 Dec ("Day 2" tests after this date are cancelled from your Medical Surveillance Order)•	Arrivals will be advised to continue with the 5-day RAT when in Hong Kong.•	Positive RAT tests - You are encouraged to report at https://www.chp.gov.hk/ratp/ for an isolation order (minimum 5-day), a care pack and eligibility to book designated clinic at Hospital Authority.

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: Two-Step Verification: How to Lock Whatsapp with Password on iPhone and AndroidTo lock your Whatsapp account with a password on iPhone and Android is by using Two-Step Verification. Therefore follow these steps:Open your WhatsApp and tap the option icon at the top.Tap Settings.Tap Account.Then, tap Two-step verification and Enable.Enter a six-digit PIN of your choice and confirm it.Also, provide an email address or tap Skip if you don’t want to add an email address.Tap Next.Confirm the email address and tap Save or Done.It is recommended you add an email address. This is useful when you want to reset the PIN or password either because you forget or it is no more secret.If there is one thing to prevent your WhatsApp from hacking, it is by enabling the Two-Step Verification

message: What is the process for Aadhaar enrolment for children of NRIs?keyboard_arrow_upPls refer to the below:Child is below 5 years of age:One of the parents/ guardian has to authenticate on behalf of the child and also give consent for enrolment of the minor by signing the enrolment form.If the child is an NRI - valid Indian passport of the child is mandatory as Proof of Identity (PoI)If the child is an Indian resident (not NRI) - any valid Proof of Relationship document (refer: https://uidai.gov.in/images/commdoc/valid_documents_list.pdf) such as Birth Certificate, along with Aadhaar of the parent/ guardian, can be used for enrolment.Child is between 5 to 18 years of age:One of the parents/ guardian has to give consent for enrolment of the minor by signing the enrolment form.If the minor is an NRI – valid Indian passport of the child is mandatory as Proof of Identity (PoI)If the minor is an Indian resident (not NRI) -No document in the name of the minor: any valid Proof of Relationship document (refer: https://uidai.gov.in/images/commdoc/valid_documents_list.pdf) such as Birth certificate can be used for enrolment under Head of Family.Minor has a document: use a valid Proof of Identity (PoI) and Proof of Address (PoA) document (like School ID card) in the child’s name for enrolment (refer: https://uidai.gov.in/images/commdoc/valid_documents_list.pdf).

name: ~ Vaibhav
message: NRIs, although they are citizens of India, are not eligible for Aadhaar Card if they have not stayed for more than 182 days or more in the last 12 months.  Upon completion of 182 days of their stay in India in the last 12 months immediately preceding the date of application for enrolment, NRIs can apply for Aadhaar Card.

Should I visit the immigration department in person or apply online again?thank you in advance !!

name: ~ Vasanth Kirubakaran
message: Hope the acknowledgement is received already. After that around 4th-6th week might have got an update. They mostly ask for a round of additional documents especially for babies & kids. If you haven't received it, u shall visit immigration department with the acknowledgement receipt and request to see the case officer. You can meet him/her and get the latest info. Thanks.
Thank you for replying..  I already submit the additional document in mid of January.

name: ~ Vasanth Kirubakaran
message: Ok. Great. Immigration team always add a disclaimer that it will take 4-6 weeks after receiving all documents. As it's already 2-3 weeks, u shall visit them/call them and mention the documents request are submitted and if any further is required. Indirectly, u will be mentioned the latest status. Can request to speedup if possible with valid reasons if any.
Okay thank you !!

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: PLEASE *DO NOT GET RRAPPED**DIGITAL FREELANCING SCAM**JObSCAM**HOTEL / FLIGHT BOOKING SCAM**PART TIME WORK SCAM**CRYPTO SCAM**MANY MORE*Few people r sending me some msg.  And asking if it’s scam as they r asking only for my bank account- they start like this and eventually make u tempted n asks for small amount *NEVER ENTER ANY*Very happy to know that few people saved their money from THOSE CHEATING GANGS and hope more and more becomes aware , so I am going to post this msg continuously as many of our friends don’t scroll old msg - pls forward to all groups -One tip in IT / part time job is the person gives you a task and asks u to deposit a small amount , don’t get into itSome sends invite code for u to participate These are what I learnt from our friends ———————One of my friend working in lawyers office told me yesterday one indian came to their office saying he has lost *HKD2,000,000*While discussing other person said someone lost *INR 30,00,000* by borrowing money by lodging his property One person from help group 1 said his friend lost *HKD600,000*I am really confused how people can give money and fall in these scamsWe have discussed this earlier but this needs more awakening, never pay money to get part time work and they pull you inside until you lose big money by tempting you*NEVER SPARE A PENNY* to any stranger.Don’t get excited , too many scams around on social mediaBe aware of asking for your *CREDIT CARD*  one of my friend told me someone posing like a Marriott staff offered some nice packages and he stopped as she had all his details except his email ID, and luckily escaped from giving his credit card , even though they ask u for small, they will charge big amount. Hope we won’t hear anymore, we need to educate our friends/relatives.Please spread this to ALL YOUR FRIENDS , HK, India , everywhere….Thanks*ADMIN**HELP GROUP HONG KONG*

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: PLEASE *DO NOT GET RRAPPED**DIGITAL FREELANCING SCAM**JObSCAM**HOTEL / FLIGHT BOOKING SCAM**PART TIME WORK SCAM**CRYPTO SCAM**MANY MORE*Few people r sending me some msg.  And asking if it’s scam as they r asking only for my bank account- they start like this and eventually make u tempted n asks for small amount *NEVER ENTER ANY*Very happy to know that few people saved their money from THOSE CHEATING GANGS and hope more and more becomes aware , so I am going to post this msg continuously as many of our friends don’t scroll old msg - pls forward to all groups -One tip in IT / part time job is the person gives you a task and asks u to deposit a small amount , don’t get into itSome sends invite code for u to participate These are what I learnt from our friends ———————One of my friend working in lawyers office told me yesterday one indian came to their office saying he has lost *HKD2,000,000*While discussing other person said someone lost *INR 30,00,000* by borrowing money by lodging his property One person from help group 1 said his friend lost *HKD600,000*I am really confused how people can give money and fall in these scamsWe have discussed this earlier but this needs more awakening, never pay money to get part time work and they pull you inside until you lose big money by tempting you*NEVER SPARE A PENNY* to any stranger.Don’t get excited , too many scams around on social mediaBe aware of asking for your *CREDIT CARD*  one of my friend told me someone posing like a Marriott staff offered some nice packages and he stopped as she had all his details except his email ID, and luckily escaped from giving his credit card , even though they ask u for small, they will charge big amount. Hope we won’t hear anymore, we need to educate our friends/relatives.Please spread this to ALL YOUR FRIENDS , HK, India , everywhere….Thanks*ADMIN**HELP GROUP HONG KONG*

And asking if it’s scam as they r asking only for my bank account- they start like this and eventually make u tempted n asks for small amount *NEVER ENTER ANY*Very happy to know that few people saved their money from THOSE CHEATING GANGS and hope more and more becomes aware , so I am going to post this msg continuously as many of our friends don’t scroll old msg - pls forward to all groups -One tip in IT / part time job is the person gives you a task and asks u to deposit a small amount , don’t get into itSome sends invite code for u to participate These are what I learnt from our friends ———————One of my friend working in lawyers office told me yesterday one indian came to their office saying he has lost *HKD2,000,000*While discussing other person said someone lost *INR 30,00,000* by borrowing money by lodging his property One person from help group 1 said his friend lost *HKD600,000*I am really confused how people can give money and fall in these scamsWe have discussed this earlier but this needs more awakening, never pay money to get part time work and they pull you inside until you lose big money by tempting you*NEVER SPARE A PENNY* to any stranger.Don’t get excited , too many scams around on social mediaBe aware of asking for your *CREDIT CARD*  one of my friend told me someone posing like a Marriott staff offered some nice packages and he stopped as she had all his details except his email ID, and luckily escaped from giving his credit card , even though they ask u for small, they will charge big amount. Hope we won’t hear anymore, we need to educate our friends/relatives.Please spread this to ALL YOUR FRIENDS , HK, India , everywhere….Thanks*ADMIN**HELP GROUP HONG KONG*

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: HK Passport / Chinese Nationality Details and run down 1. Steps2. ExpenseHK Passport & Nationality details ###########Applied nationality 11 Dec 2015Paid processing fee $1730now Wait - 10 month (sep-oct2016)later:  Receive Letter (approval in principle, now you get one year window to reconsider and actually apply)Give up Nationality at Indian Consulate Contact Immegration and change HKID with 3-starsThen apply Hk Passport <<<IMPORTANT >>>APPLICATION STATUS - if some change happens which impact application then inform Immegration.OFFICER SAID: If you move from your house then inform (otherwise letter will go to old address)<<STEPS>>>Step 1.Apply for Naturalization as a Chinese National.Apply at Immigration office in Wanchai on 4th Floor.Bring completed form and all original certificates.Officer will interview in Cantonese (English also ok) and check all documents. If officer is satisfied, pay 50% deposit and wait for their information.Processing time was 9 months.At approval, Immigration dep’t will send approval notice by mail.Step 2.Renounce Indian passport.Apply at Indian consulate 9:30-12:00Bring:Form 17 X 2 copies. Sign form in front of the officer.Passport size 2”X2” photos X 2 in white background. (Fotomax at United Centre) Nationalization approval letter copy. Latest Passport and copyAll Old Passports original. Pay $1170 advance.Collect renunciation cert, signed form 17 and cancelled last Passport on the following day. Remark: they Didn't check old Passports and no need residence proof. But they can ask all this.Step 3.Apply for Chinese Naturalization Cert.Apply at Immigration Tower 4th FloorBring:Naturalization approval letterRenounce Indian Passport Cert and signed form 17Pay balance 50% fee.Receive Naturalization cert immediately.Received another sealed envelope containing letter for new HKID .Step 4.Apply for new HKID. (Apply immediately after receiving Naturalization certificate as they have walk in quota in the morning)Apply at 8th FloorBring:Naturalization certificateSealed envelopeHK Permanent ID.Write Chinese name and sign in front of the officer in Chinese.Pay HKD420Will receive HKID acknowledgement and receive new HKID in 3 weeks.Cannot speed up.<TIP> for parallel application to Apply ‘Certificate of registered Particulars’ @HK$425 after HKID, takes 4-5 weeks. It is needed to apply for China Card (not for HKSAR Passport). Better enquire whether it can be requested at the time of applying HKID card?Step 5.Apply for HK Passport. (Apply *immediately* after applying for new HKID as they have walk in quota in the morning)Apply at 4th FloorBring:Completed formAcknowledgement of HKIDNaturalization certificateRenounce Indian passport Certificate and signed form 17Pay HKD480 for 48pages.Can speed up to 4 working days but need evidence of urgent business travel like e-ticket, company letter and name card.Normal processing time is 2 weeksStep 6.Apply for Home return card <it can take Many Months ~6-8 months. In my case it was available within a month. I guess,  those who travel frequently to China gets it much much later as it happened with my friend >Apply at CTS Lek Yuen.Take photo there $40Bring:Temporary HKID and 2 copiesHK passport and 2 copiesRight of Abode letter issued at the time of receiving Permanent ID and 2 copiesNaturalization cert and 2 copiesAll old Indian passports.Renunciation of Indian Passport Certificate and signed form 17 and 2 copies.Officer will check records of first entry to Mainland China, first entry to HKSAR under Employment visa, Last HKSAR employment visa, if any job change in between, Current China visa status etc and prepare a statement on your behalf.Check all and sign. Applied temporary permit in parallel.Step 7.Apply for OCI (30-Dec)Apply onlinePrint a copy of online application formSend online application Reference number to Indian consulate by e-mail and request for an interview.Received interview appointment e-mail (They reply after few days + Give appointment after few weeks :-{{  )Attend interview and the officer checked all documents in original.Officer will inform you, that you’ll get email after few days whether your application is approved (meaning processable). Only after that you can come to pay for OCI fee. Fees is only acceptable on FRIDAY and in Cash. No other day , no online transfer , no advance payment :-{{.  Can request your friend etc to go and deposit fees if you are travelling.Application got approved in 2 days. Submitted $2170 fee on Friday (no need to go in person).OCI fee can be paid only on Fridays from 9:30 to 12 noon.After paying fee, it takes 35 days to get OCI and lifelong visa.Check OCI status online. When it shows Documents rec’d at Hong Kong date than go to Indian Consulate on any working day from 9:30AM to 12noon to collect OCI card and lifelong visa.Collected OCI card and lifelong visa.#2 ExpenseA) Nationality @Application -  HK1760B) India Passport Surrender / Renounce - HK$ 1170 c) nationality @Approval - $1760D) HkId (adding chinese name )$460E) HK Passport (1 month) - F) India OCI - HK$ 2170G) Certificate of Registered Particulars -HK$ 425 (fo tan)(3-4 week)H) China Entry Card-$550~ Hk$ 8000f

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: *"Sil Suwandai - Hela Diviyayi" ~ Authentic Sri Lankan Cuisine Ceremony Offering to Lord Buddha, Monks and Devotees.*Under the proposal and guidance of the Regional Food Promotion National Program of the President's Office, the Authentic Sri Lankan Cuisine Ceremony will be held on *Sunday, August 27, at the premises of "Ceylon Farm Village" in Sheung Shui,* affiliated to the Sri Lankan Buddhist Cultural Center in Hong Kong, according to the concept of "Sil Suwandai - Hela Diviyay ~ The Buddhist Way of Life”Authentic Sri Lankan cuisine is a vibrant and diverse culinary tapestry that reflects the island nation's rich history, cultural influences, and unique geography.The cuisine showcases an array of aromatic spices, tropical ingredients, and traditional cooking techniques passed down through generations.Staple ingredients in Sri Lankan cooking are as diverse as the island nation's rich cultural heritage. Rice, a dietary staple, takes center stage in almost every meal, often accompanied by an array of aromatic curries. Coconut and its derivatives play a crucial role in Sri Lankan cuisine, with coconut milk and grated coconut lending their creamy texture to curries and desserts.Spices such as cinnamon, cardamom, cloves, and cumin infuse dishes with deep flavors while adding a distinct aroma.These spices not only provide an explosion of taste but also offer various health benefits due to their natural medicinal properties. The artful use of spices reflects the mastery and creativity of Sri Lankan chefs who skillfully blend these ingredients to create tantalizing culinary experiences.Farmers in Sri Lanka offer their first batch of produce to the village Buddhist temple and traditional households offer the first portion of their daily meal to Lord Buddha.*We cordially invite you to experience this journey, offering and tasting the meals which created using Authentic Sri Lankan Ingredients, according to traditional recipes.*Ceylon farm village ~ "Ape Gama"Sri Lankan Buddhist Cultural Centre - Hong Kong530 Hang Tau Rd, Kwu tung, Sheung Shui.53608945 / 96183249 / 53437269 / 95785253 / 56173856info@slbcchk.com

name: ~ Butt hina
message: Dear Parents, Are you feeling overwhelmed by the Primary One Admission (POA) process? Or perhaps you're unsure about how to best prepare your child for the transition from kindergarten to primary school? We understand the challenges you may be facing, and we are here to provide you with the information you need! We represent Oxfam and have an exciting opportunity we'd like to share with you. We have created a video tutorial that demonstrates how to properly fill in the form for a discretionary place. If you're interested in gaining a deeper understanding of the POA system and acquiring valuable educational resources to teach Chinese to your children, we invite you to participate in a brief survey that will only take approximately 5 minutes of your time. By completing the survey, you will be eligible to receive a curated selection of educational materials that we will distribute to you. These resources are designed to enhance your teaching capabilities and provide valuable insights into teaching Chinese effectively. To take advantage of this offer and access the educational resources, kindly fill out the survey at your earliest convenience. Your participation will greatly contribute to the success of our initiative and enable us to better tailor the distribution of resources to meet your specific needs. Thank you for your interest and support. We look forward to your response and the opportunity to assist you in your educational endeavors. If you have any questions about POA system or about the survey, please contact Ms. Yip at 6110 6408. The Video of Discretionary Place Form Filling: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Ai3fCW74ee4fSavSyHu7uYii70WG17JS/view?usp=sharingGoogle survey Link:https://forms.gle/Qa7Je855unHSZsDz6 Best regards,The Oxfam Team

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: Hello RaoHappy to share the Indian  helper employment contract renew process:1. Get the ID 441, blue form from the HK immigration department - 4 of these.2. Take BLS appointment for form filling (in case of doubts) and submission back to back.3. Once form is fully filled, sign by both helper & employer & submit it at BLS for attestation by Indian consulate - takes 3-5 working days4. Once you receive the form - 3 copies as Indian consulate will keep 1 for its record, make sure it’s attested fully. In next step can submit to HK immigration  for online renewal - https://www.immd.gov.hk/eng/services/visas/fdh/smartrenewal.htmlThe above website will first ask details of helper name, age, DOB, nationality etc. (upload below scanned document HKID, existing visa pages, passport front, back & last travel stamp if any) plus the scan copy of new employment form. You can apply for extension of stay which means after 1 year of the next contract your helper will need to travel outside to home or in some cases if agreed between employer & helper the visa can be extended again without travel, to activate the remaining 1 year of the visa. -The online form other parts are employer details on HKID, passport (if on working visa), address proof through utility bills - not older than 3 months, Financial proof - Bank statement or payslips - best to give 3 months record. 5. The HK immigration step for approval takes 10-15 business days, however in 2-3 business days you should receive acknowledgment of submitting application.6. HK immigration might contact directly on phone or email in case any further docs are needed. Once the processing completes you can download the evisa by paying online.

name: ~ Raghav Rao
message: Total fees with above process is:BLS charge approx: 300-500 HKDVISA fees: 230 HKDPS: above case have not bought tickets yet as it’s an year extension with helper to travel after 1 year to activate next half of the visa.

name: ~ RR
message: As per my understanding for travelling you need passport and visa. You should get in touch with immigration department and explain your situation. And you should apply for HKID and keep the application receipt. Probably when you are back to HK, you can show the receipt to the immigration officer if its asked for. Worst case postpone your travel. We can give some information but we dont represent immigration and better to get in touch with them soon. India immigration side, till my HKID was not permanent, they always used to check my work VISA.No idea about urgent issuance of HKID by immigration department.May be others can share their insights.In either case get in touch with immigration department where you will get first hand information. HK Govt people are very helpful most of the time.
